    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A colorless crystalline organic compound that is a product of protein metabolism in mammals. Urea can break hydrogen bonds and destabilize collagen. In conservation practice, this interaction reduces hardness and deformation in parchment, leather, and related materials.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
